WEBVTT

01:20.081 --> 01:21.750
THANK YOU, LORD.

02:01.956 --> 02:03.249
Charles:
WHAT WE GOT OUT THERE

02:03.249 --> 02:05.418
IS 100 ACRES OF WHEAT
READY TO HARVEST.

02:05.418 --> 02:07.921
COME ON, EVERYBODY,
WRITE THAT DOWN--100.

02:10.757 --> 02:14.719
AND IT OUGHT TO YIELD ABOUT...OH,
35 BUSHELS TO THE ACRE.

02:14.719 --> 02:16.429
THANK YOU.

02:16.429 --> 02:19.891
AND RIGHT NOW WHEAT'S SELLING FOR
JUST AROUND 75 CENTS A BUSHEL.

02:19.891 --> 02:21.810
NOW, HOW MUCH MONEY
IS THAT?

02:25.104 --> 02:27.315
- I'VE GOT IT.
- SO HAVE I.

02:27.315 --> 02:30.527
Both: $2,625!

02:30.527 --> 02:32.028
RIGHT.

02:32.028 --> 02:34.155
IT'S ALMOST TOO
WONDERFUL TO BE TRUE.

02:34.155 --> 02:36.115
DO YOU KNOW WHAT THAT
WILL MEAN FOR US?

02:36.115 --> 02:39.661
NEW DRESSES FOR MY GIRLS,
TO START WITH.

02:39.661 --> 02:42.831
A NICE WARM COAT FOR YOU,
CURTAINS FOR THE WINDOWS.

02:42.831 --> 02:44.791
BOOTS FOR YOU.

02:44.791 --> 02:46.835
THE VERY FIRST NICKEL
WE SPEND GOES ON BOOTS.

02:46.835 --> 02:49.921
WHAT'S THE MATTER WITH THESE? THEY WERE
JUST STARTING TO GET COMFORTABLE ON ME.

02:49.921 --> 02:51.464
[ALL LAUGH]

02:51.464 --> 02:54.133
I WAS AFRAID ONE MORNING YOU
WERE GOING TO PULL THEM UP,

02:54.133 --> 02:56.219
AND THEY'D SLIDE
CLEAR UP TO YOUR KNEES.

02:56.219 --> 02:58.513
COME ON. LET'S MAKE A LIST.
EVERYTHING WE NEED.

02:58.513 --> 03:01.808
START RIGHT OUT WITH
DRESSES FOR YOU GIRLS.

03:01.808 --> 03:03.351
SHOES FOR EVERYONE.
THAT'S A MUST.

03:03.351 --> 03:05.895
ALL RIGHT. SHOES.
CURTAINS FOR THE WINDOWS.

03:05.895 --> 03:07.063
GOT THAT?

03:07.063 --> 03:08.189
YES, PA.

03:08.189 --> 03:09.732
NOT SO FAST.

03:09.732 --> 03:11.150
MA NEEDS SOME
NEW DISHES AND--

03:11.150 --> 03:13.820
I'M WRITING DOWN A ROCKING
HORSE FOR CARRIE.

03:13.820 --> 03:16.281
A ROCKING HORSE
FOR CARRIE!

03:16.281 --> 03:19.909
YOU KNOW, THAT REMINDED ME OF SOMETHING
THAT JUST POPPED CLEAN OUT OF MY HEAD.

03:19.909 --> 03:21.452
WHAT IS IT?

03:21.452 --> 03:23.997
YOU COME WITH ME, AND I'LL SHOW YOU.
COME ON...EVERYBODY.

03:32.839 --> 03:34.591
Mary: WHAT IS IT, PA?

03:36.342 --> 03:38.177
Laura: I CAN'T WAIT.

03:41.347 --> 03:43.182
WON'T YOU
TELL US, PA?

03:43.182 --> 03:44.684
PLEASE?

04:00.366 --> 04:02.493
Caroline: OH, CHARLES!

04:03.411 --> 04:06.831
Mary:
OH, PA! HORSES!

04:06.831 --> 04:08.708
Laura: LOOK
AT THEM, MARY!

04:08.708 --> 04:10.209
WHAT A SURPRISE!

04:10.209 --> 04:11.753
BOY, AREN'T
THEY PRETTY!

04:11.753 --> 04:15.298
BE CAREFUL TILL THEY GET
TO KNOW YOU A LITTLE BIT.

04:17.675 --> 04:19.427
CHARLES,
YOU DIDN'T EVEN HINT.

04:19.427 --> 04:21.262
I WANTED IT
TO BE A SURPRISE.

04:21.262 --> 04:22.555
IT CERTAINLY IS.

04:22.555 --> 04:24.223
WELL, THEY'RE GOOD,
STOUT ANIMALS,

04:24.223 --> 04:25.725
BOTH OF THEM.

04:25.725 --> 04:27.560
ONLY 8 YEARS OLD. GOT A LOT
OF GOOD YEARS LEFT IN THEM.

04:27.560 --> 04:30.605
Girls:
THEY'RE So PRETTY!

04:30.605 --> 04:32.732
MADE A GOOD TRADE WITH
HANSON, TOO, ON THE OXEN.

04:32.732 --> 04:34.776
WE'LL BE ABLE TO PAY THE BALANCE
AS SOON AS I SELL THE WHEAT.

04:34.776 --> 04:36.194
OH, THAT'S GOOD.

04:36.194 --> 04:38.404
IT'S SOMETHING
WE REALLY NEEDED.

04:38.404 --> 04:40.573
I KNOW.

04:40.573 --> 04:42.575
I'M SO GLAD!

04:42.575 --> 04:43.785
SO AM I...

04:43.785 --> 04:45.161
SO NOW, MRS. INGALLS,

04:45.161 --> 04:46.788
I'LL BE ABLE TO DRIVE
YOU TO CHURCH IN STYLE.

04:46.788 --> 04:48.414
CHARLES!

04:49.832 --> 04:51.918
[THUNDER]

05:16.359 --> 05:18.069
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

05:21.114 --> 05:22.699
UH, NOTHING.

05:22.699 --> 05:25.868
IT'S JUST A LITTLE RAIN.
WE COULD USE IT.

05:33.835 --> 05:35.503
WHAT ABOUT THE WHEAT?

05:37.964 --> 05:40.633
OH, IT'S REAL GOOD
FOR THE WHEAT...

05:40.633 --> 05:44.303
LONG AS IT'S STANDING,
SOAK IT REAL GOOD.

05:50.476 --> 05:53.062
STILL GOT A LITTLE
FIRE THERE GOING.

05:53.062 --> 05:55.523
I'LL MAKE YOU
SOME COFFEE, HUH?

05:55.523 --> 05:57.567
I'LL GET IT.

06:01.571 --> 06:03.573
GO ON. SIT DOWN.

06:12.582 --> 06:14.751
REALLY COMING DOWN.

06:14.751 --> 06:16.669
MMM-

06:18.796 --> 06:20.840
THAT'S GOOD.

06:23.259 --> 06:26.387
WE COULD USE
SOME RAIN.

06:26.387 --> 06:28.556
LONG AS IT DOESN'T SOAK
THAT FIELD SO MUCH

06:28.556 --> 06:30.975
WE CAN'T GET MR. HANSON'S
NEW REAPER IN THERE.

06:30.975 --> 06:33.227
HE'S GOT A NEW
McCORNHCK REAPER.

06:33.227 --> 06:35.229
I TELL YOU ABOUT IT?

06:36.522 --> 06:37.940
YES.

06:40.026 --> 06:42.195
THAT'S A FINE MACHINE.

06:42.195 --> 06:44.697
[THUNDER]

06:49.827 --> 06:51.871
[WHINING]

06:57.794 --> 06:59.962
[TAPPING ON ROOF]

07:09.555 --> 07:10.765
HAIL!

07:15.895 --> 07:17.522
[CRYING]

07:27.782 --> 07:29.659
[CAROLINE MURMURING]

07:29.659 --> 07:31.744
[THUNDER]

07:53.015 --> 07:55.560
I'M SOAKED TO THE SKIN.

07:56.936 --> 07:59.730
GOT PRETTY COLD OUT THERE,
I'LL TELL YOU.

07:59.730 --> 08:02.441
THIS COFFEE'S GOING
TO TASTE GOOD.

08:13.452 --> 08:16.038
LOOKS LIKE THE STORM'S
ABOUT OVER.

08:26.632 --> 08:29.218
THE WHEAT'S GONE.

08:39.312 --> 08:42.648
LOOK, THERE'S NOTHING TO BE SOLEMN ABOUT.
I GUESS YOU...

08:44.483 --> 08:48.029
MIGHT SAY THAT WE'RE
BACK WHERE WE STARTED.

08:49.488 --> 08:51.490
I MEAN, IT'S
JUST ONE HARVEST.

08:52.950 --> 08:56.329
NOW, WHAT'S ONE HARVEST
IN A MAN'S LIFE, HUH?

08:59.123 --> 09:00.958
IT'S NOTHING.

09:00.958 --> 09:02.293
OH!

09:13.012 --> 09:15.973
OLLIE! OLLIE!
YOU TAKE A REST.

09:15.973 --> 09:18.851
WE CAN'T HEAR
OURSELVES TALK.

09:18.851 --> 09:20.019
LIKE I SAID, KONIG.
I KNOW.

09:20.019 --> 09:22.730
EVERYBODY HERE IS
IN THE SAME BOAT.

09:22.730 --> 09:25.024
THE HAIL DON'T PLAY
NO FAVORITES.

09:25.024 --> 09:26.901
IF FALLS
ON EVERY MAN ALIKE.

09:26.901 --> 09:29.695
THERE AIN'T NO ONE
FOR 50 MILES AROUND

09:29.695 --> 09:31.155
THAT'S GONNA MAKE A CROP,

09:31.155 --> 09:33.407
BUT I WANT TO DO
SOMETHING ABOUT IT,

09:33.407 --> 09:35.826
BUT THERE'S NOT ANYTHING
THAT I CAN DO

09:35.826 --> 09:36.994
EXCEPT WEEP.

09:36.994 --> 09:40.748
I CAN'T SPEAK
FOR WILLIAMS HERE,

09:40.748 --> 09:46.545
BUT WHAT I'VE GOT IN MIND
IS A BUSINESS PROPOSITION.

09:46.545 --> 09:50.716
YOU LOAN ME $200,
AND I'LL PAY INTEREST.

09:50.716 --> 09:51.926
CONFOUND IT, MAN!

09:51.926 --> 09:53.886
THAT IS JUST WHAT
I WANT TO DO,

09:53.886 --> 09:56.722
BUT I HAVEN'T GOT
$200 TO LOAN,

09:56.722 --> 09:58.766
AND WITH NO WHEAT
TO MILL,

09:58.766 --> 10:00.768
I AIN'T GONNA GET IT.

10:06.899 --> 10:10.528
Williams:
MR. HANSON.

10:10.528 --> 10:13.406
MY WIFE BESS,
SHE TOOK SICK.

10:13.406 --> 10:15.408
WITH 5 KIDS
TO FEED AND ALL,

10:15.408 --> 10:16.659
I JUST DON'T KNOW
HOW IN THE WORLD

10:16.659 --> 10:18.202
I'M GONNA GET BY
UNLESS YOU CAN--

10:18.202 --> 10:23.124
JIM...I'M SORRY.

10:23.124 --> 10:25.084
THE ANSWER IS NO.

10:36.429 --> 10:37.722
HUP!

10:41.267 --> 10:43.227
CHARLIE.

10:43.227 --> 10:46.147
GUESS THAT'S ABOUT THE
QUICKEST DEAL YOU EVER MADE...

10:46.147 --> 10:50.443
SELLING A TEAM OF HORSES ONE
DAY, GETTING THEM BACK THE NEXT.

10:50.443 --> 10:53.779
I DON'T LIKE
THAT KIND OF DEAL.

10:53.779 --> 10:56.574
WELL, NEITHER DO I.

10:56.574 --> 10:59.410
ALWAYS DREAMED OF OWNING
A TEAM LIKE THIS.

10:59.410 --> 11:03.164
BUT A MAN CAN'T KEEP
WHAT HE CAN'T PAY FOR.

11:03.164 --> 11:05.666
WHAT ARE YOU
GOING TO DO?

11:05.666 --> 11:08.753
I'LL GO LOOKING FOR WORK,
LIKE EVERYBODY ELSE.

11:08.753 --> 11:11.422
GOT TO HAVE CASH
FOR WINTER.

11:14.550 --> 11:15.926
I'LL SEE YOU.

11:15.926 --> 11:17.928
TAKE CARE.

11:28.647 --> 11:33.569
I DON'T KNOW HOW FAR I'M GOING TO
HAVE TO GO-- 100 MILES, MAYBE MORE.

11:33.569 --> 11:38.657
THERE'LL BE A LOT OF MEN LOOKING FOR
WORK, AND NOT MANY JOBS AROUND.

11:38.657 --> 11:40.159
YOU WILL WRITE TO US?

11:40.159 --> 11:42.244
OH, YEAH. I'LL WRITE JUST
AS SOON AS I GET SETTLED.

11:42.244 --> 11:45.456
MIGHT HAVE TO GO AS FAR
AS SLEEPY EYE OR MANKATO,

11:45.456 --> 11:48.834
SO IT COULD BE A WHILE BEFORE
THAT FIRST LETTER COMES.

12:00.304 --> 12:01.680
THANK YOU.

12:17.780 --> 12:19.532
I'LL MISS YOU.

12:21.700 --> 12:24.412
GIVE CARRIE
A KISS FOR ME, HUH?

12:33.337 --> 12:34.713
LOVE YOU.

12:34.713 --> 12:35.923
OH!

13:55.294 --> 13:58.214
LOOK, I'VE GOT TO BE GOING,
LOVE, THAT'S ALL. ALL RIGHT?

13:58.214 --> 14:01.592
PA! YOU FORGOT
SOMETHING.

14:01.592 --> 14:03.928
ONE MORE TIME CAN'T HURT, PEG.
I'LL BE CAREFUL.

14:03.928 --> 14:05.387
THAT'LL BE THE DAY.

14:05.387 --> 14:08.307
YOU'LL BLOW YOURSELF
TO BITS, MORE LIKE IT.

14:08.307 --> 14:09.642
SEE IF I CARE.

14:09.642 --> 14:11.560
YOU'D CARE.
I KNOW YOU WOULD.

14:11.560 --> 14:15.439
BUT I'LL BE COMING BACK TO
FARM FOR THE REST OF MY LIFE.

14:15.439 --> 14:16.649
YOU...

14:16.649 --> 14:18.817
CAN YOU MANAGE THE FARM
WHILE I'M GONE,

14:18.817 --> 14:20.986
OR WILL YOU HAVE
TO HIRE HELP?

14:20.986 --> 14:22.446
NEVER HIRE HELP.

14:22.446 --> 14:26.242
I COULD MANAGE THIS FARM AS
GOOD AS YOU--MAYBE BETTER.

14:26.242 --> 14:27.993
[LAUGHING]

14:27.993 --> 14:30.621
ALL RIGHT, THEN.
HOW ABOUT IT?

14:30.621 --> 14:32.248
ALL RIGHT.

14:33.207 --> 14:35.793
Boy: LET'S GO. LET'S GO!

14:35.793 --> 14:37.836
Man: COME ON! COME ON!

14:37.836 --> 14:40.005
Um-u

14:40.005 --> 14:42.174
HEY...

14:42.174 --> 14:46.845
YOU TAKE GOOD CARE OF YOUR MOTHER
WHILE I'M AWAY, UNDERSTAND?

14:46.845 --> 14:48.514
YEAH, PA.

15:03.737 --> 15:05.573
I LOVE YOU, WOMAN.

15:10.786 --> 15:12.705
TAKE CARE.

16:00.252 --> 16:02.254
CHARLES INGALLS.

16:02.254 --> 16:04.089
JACK PETERS.

16:04.089 --> 16:06.133
HAD THIS THING TIED
UP WITH A STRING,

16:06.133 --> 16:08.052
BUT THE STRING
WORE OUT.

16:08.052 --> 16:09.887
JUST GOING TO HAVE
TO FLAP, I GUESS.

16:09.887 --> 16:13.223
NO, IT AIN'T. THAT'S WHAT I WAS
TRYING TO CATCH UP WITH YOU FOR.

16:13.223 --> 16:15.184
GOT A PIECE
OF RAWHIDE HERE.

16:15.184 --> 16:17.186
OUGHT TO HOLD IT
FOR A WHILE.

16:17.186 --> 16:19.897
HEY...YEAH!
YEAH, IT'S GOOD.

16:24.777 --> 16:26.862
WHERE ARE YOU
HEADING?

16:26.862 --> 16:28.530
WORK.

16:28.530 --> 16:31.700
SAME HERE. I GUESS
EVERYBODY IS.

16:31.700 --> 16:33.827
I SUPPOSE.

16:33.827 --> 16:35.245
THAT'LL HOLD IT.

16:35.245 --> 16:37.456
ALL I CAN GIVE YOU
IS MY THANKS.

16:37.456 --> 16:39.833
AND YOUR COMPANIONSHIP.

16:39.833 --> 16:41.627
YOU GOT IT.

16:51.428 --> 16:53.389
[LAUGHING]

17:43.188 --> 17:45.232
Jack: TASTES GREAT,
SMELLS GREAT.

17:45.232 --> 17:48.026
A SMELL LIKE THIS ON THE WIND
WILL BRING THE BEARS OUT

17:48.026 --> 17:50.863
FOR A MILE...
MAYBE MORE.

17:52.614 --> 17:55.659
[SWEDISH ACCENT]
HELLO. MY NAME IS JACOB.

17:55.659 --> 17:58.662
IS IT ALL RIGHT
I SHARE YOUR FIRE?

17:58.662 --> 18:00.956
SURE ENOUGH.
COME ON, SIT DOWN.

18:03.083 --> 18:05.210
MY NAME IS CHARLES INGALLS.
THAT'S JACK PETERS.

18:05.210 --> 18:08.088
MR. INGALLS,
MR. PETERS.

18:08.088 --> 18:10.048
HOW ABOUT
SOMETHING TO EAT?

18:10.048 --> 18:12.593
NO. NO, THANK YOU.
I HAD FOOD.

18:12.593 --> 18:14.762
WE GOT PLENTY.

18:32.738 --> 18:34.656
WHAT DO YOU THINK,
JACK?

18:36.241 --> 18:38.076
HUNGRIER
THAN WE WERE.

18:38.076 --> 18:40.287
BIG AS HE IS,
HUNGRIER.

18:42.039 --> 18:43.832
COME ON.

18:43.832 --> 18:46.376
JOIN US. JUST GOING
TO GO TO WASTE,

18:46.376 --> 18:50.005
UNLESS YOU CAN FIGURE OUT A WAY
TO PUT STEW IN YOUR POCKET.

18:50.005 --> 18:52.090
[LAUGHING]

18:52.090 --> 18:53.717
THANK YOU.

19:00.140 --> 19:02.684
YOU COOKED...
I'LL CLEAN UP.

19:02.684 --> 19:06.563
I DON'T THINK YOU'RE GOING
TO HAVE TO CLEAN UP.

19:06.563 --> 19:08.106
[LAUGHING]

19:11.276 --> 19:12.820
THANK YOU.

19:14.446 --> 19:15.739
[SIGHS]

19:15.739 --> 19:17.366
[CLEARS TH ROAT]

19:22.412 --> 19:24.456
[CHUCKLES]

19:34.967 --> 19:37.177
[TOSSES BOOTS AWAY]

19:37.177 --> 19:38.554
HEY!

19:38.554 --> 19:40.472
WITH THOSE BOOTS, YOU'RE
THE SAME AS BAREFOOT.

19:40.472 --> 19:43.517
ALL RIGHT, BUT THEY'RE
THE ONLY BOOTS I'VE GOT.

19:43.517 --> 19:45.769
I TAN HIDES.

19:45.769 --> 19:49.398
MAKE BOOTS AT NIGHT
AFTER FARM WORK.

19:50.732 --> 19:52.693
BRING TWO PAIR
TO SELL.

19:52.693 --> 19:54.820
RIGHT AWAY,
GOT A CUSTOMER.

19:54.820 --> 19:56.655
HMM?

19:57.698 --> 20:00.242
THEY'RE
FINE-LOOKING BOOTS.

20:05.205 --> 20:07.499
FIT ME LIKE THEY
WERE MADE FOR ME.

20:08.834 --> 20:11.003
JA.

20:14.715 --> 20:17.009
I CAN'T PAY YOU
FOR THEM.

20:18.260 --> 20:19.720
SOMEDAY.

20:21.013 --> 20:22.598
SOMEDAY.

20:26.685 --> 20:29.062
ARE YOU MEN DEAD SET
ON WORKING HARVEST?

20:29.062 --> 20:33.191
THERE'S GOING TO BE A LOT OF MEN
LOOKING FOR A FEW JOBS, YOU KNOW.

20:33.191 --> 20:35.027
YOU MAY NOT FIND ONE.

20:35.027 --> 20:37.029
WELL, WE DON'T
HAVE MUCH CHOICE.

20:37.029 --> 20:40.699
WOULD YOU WORK IN A QUARRY...
MINING HARD ROCK?

20:40.699 --> 20:42.367
THAT'S WHERE I'M GOING.

20:42.367 --> 20:46.747
I KNOW THE BOSS WELL ENOUGH
TO GET YOU A SHOT AT A JOB.

20:46.747 --> 20:48.540
EVER DO ANY
DOUBLE JACKING?

20:49.833 --> 20:51.376
WHAT'S THAT?

20:51.376 --> 20:53.170
A DOUBLE JACK'S
A SLEDGEHAMMER.

20:53.170 --> 20:55.339
YOU SWING IT WITH
BOTH YOUR HANDS.

20:55.339 --> 20:57.049
YOU HAMMER A DRILL
IN THE ROCK,

20:57.049 --> 20:59.468
AND YOU MAKE HOLES
TO PUT THE DYNAMITE IN.

20:59.468 --> 21:01.720
IT'S RISKY.
IT'S HARD WORK.

21:01.720 --> 21:05.057
AND YOU'LL HAVE TO SHOW YOU
CAN DO IT TO GET THE JOB.

21:05.057 --> 21:08.435
DO YOU WANT TO TRY IT?

21:08.435 --> 21:11.146
OH, JUMPIN' JIMINY,
I DO.

21:12.606 --> 21:14.066
SO DO I.

21:14.066 --> 21:16.693
YOU'LL GET A CHANCE.

21:17.945 --> 21:20.072
[CLANK CLAN K]

21:43.011 --> 21:45.013
Jack: SWAN BENSON
AND ROOF TAYLOR.

21:45.013 --> 21:47.015
BEST DOUBLE JACK TEAM
AROUND HERE.

21:47.015 --> 21:49.935
THEY'RE DRILLING HOLES SO WE
CAN DYNAMITE THAT BIG SLAB

21:49.935 --> 21:51.853
INTO PIECES SMALL
ENOUGH TO HANDLE.

21:51.853 --> 21:54.606
THEN THE TEAMS HAUL IT
OFF TO THE RAILROAD.

21:54.606 --> 21:56.817
RAILROAD HAULS IT OFF
TO WHERE STONEMASONS

21:56.817 --> 21:59.903
WILL USE IT FOR BRIDGE
PIERS AND BUILDINGS.

21:59.903 --> 22:01.279
NOW WATCH.

22:01.279 --> 22:04.074
[CLANK CLAN K]

22:04.074 --> 22:07.327
THE MAN WITH THE DOUBLE JACK...ALL
HE NEEDS IS A GOOD EYE.

22:07.327 --> 22:10.622
THE MAN HOLDING THE DRILL...
STRONG NERVES.

22:10.622 --> 22:12.249
THAT'S IT.

22:14.459 --> 22:16.753
WHAT IF
THE HAMMER MISS?

22:16.753 --> 22:19.006
IF THE HAMMER MISS?

22:19.006 --> 22:20.465
[LAUGHS]

22:20.465 --> 22:22.384
THE MAN HOLDING
THE DRILL

22:22.384 --> 22:25.262
WILL HAVE TO PICK HIS
NOSE WITH HIS ELBOW.

22:35.522 --> 22:39.067
Jack: CHARLES, JAKE...
BOSS TOM CASSIDY.

22:39.067 --> 22:39.985
HOWDY.

22:39.985 --> 22:41.820
Charles:
HOW ARE YOU?

22:41.820 --> 22:43.488
MR. CASSIDY.

22:43.488 --> 22:46.992
PETERS TELLS ME YOU'RE A DOUBLE
JACK TEAM LOOKING FOR WORK.

22:46.992 --> 22:48.368
HMM?

22:48.368 --> 22:50.954
THAT'S RIGHT.

22:52.497 --> 22:54.458
ROOF! SWAN!

22:54.458 --> 22:56.084
SIT DOWN FOR A MINUTE.

22:56.084 --> 22:59.504
GOT A NEW TEAM HERE,
WANTS TO SHOW THEIR STUFF.

22:59.504 --> 23:01.423
YOU CAN USE
THEIR TOOLS.

23:01.423 --> 23:02.841
THANK YOU.

23:12.434 --> 23:14.853
YOU HAMMER,
MR. INGALLS.

24:05.445 --> 24:07.864
CHANGE AROUND.

24:52.826 --> 24:55.287
Cassidy: COME ON!
PICK IT UP, PICK IT UP!

24:55.287 --> 24:57.455
GET THE SWING
IN THAT THING!

24:59.666 --> 25:03.920
LOOK, UH...MY PARTNER AND I WORK A
LOT FASTER WHEN WE'RE GETTING PAID.

25:11.928 --> 25:13.847
ALL RIGHT,
YOU GOT THE JOB.

25:13.847 --> 25:16.266
GO ON...SIGN ON,
PICK UP YOUR TOOLS.

25:16.266 --> 25:20.312
COME ON, YOU TWO. BACK TO WORK.
IT'S OVER. GET ON WITH IT.

25:23.648 --> 25:25.066
[LAUGHING]

25:25.066 --> 25:28.320
GLAD YOU HAVE HANDS
STILL TO SHAKE WITH.

25:38.496 --> 25:40.749
GOOD MORNING, LADIES.

25:41.958 --> 25:43.627
LADIES!

25:43.627 --> 25:46.171
MAY I HAVE YOUR
ATTENTION, PLEASE?

25:47.297 --> 25:50.133
WELL, I'M GLAD SO MANY
OF YOU COULD COME.

25:50.133 --> 25:51.801
I THANK YOU FOR IT.

25:51.801 --> 25:54.346
WE ALL HAVE
THE SAME PROBLEM--

25:54.346 --> 25:56.348
FEEDING OUR FAMILIES
NEXT WINTER.

25:56.348 --> 25:59.226
AND YOU'VE SHOWN
BY COMING HERE TODAY

25:59.226 --> 26:03.104
THAT YOU THINK WE'LL ALL FARE
BETTER IF WE WORK TOGETHER.

26:03.104 --> 26:06.816
DOES ANYBODY WANT
TO SAY ANYTHING?

26:06.816 --> 26:09.027
YES, I DO.

26:09.027 --> 26:11.154
I'D LIKE TO SAY THAT I DON'T
THINK lT'D BE SENSIBLE

26:11.154 --> 26:13.114
TO TRY AND HARVEST
ANY OF THAT WHEAT,

26:13.114 --> 26:15.367
IF THAT'S WHAT
WE'RE GOING TO DO.

26:15.367 --> 26:18.161
THAT'S WHAT
WE'RE GOING TO DO.

26:18.161 --> 26:19.537
WELL, MY SAKES...

26:19.537 --> 26:22.082
IT'S ALL LYING FLAT
ON THE GROUND.

26:22.082 --> 26:24.668
I KNOW IT'S LYING
FLAT ON THE GROUND.

26:24.668 --> 26:27.462
I DIDN'T SAY IT WOULD
BE EASY TO HARVEST IT.

26:27.462 --> 26:29.422
EASY!

26:29.422 --> 26:32.509
GRACIOUS...l JUST
DON'T THINK WE CAN.

26:32.509 --> 26:35.845
WE CAN IF WE WANT TO
BADLY ENOUGH.

26:35.845 --> 26:37.055
HOW?

26:37.055 --> 26:39.266
WE'LL HAVE TO GO
INTO THE FIELDS,

26:39.266 --> 26:41.810
PICK UP A FEW STALKS
AT A TIME, BY HAND,

26:41.810 --> 26:44.729
RAKE SOME OF IT,
PUT IT INTO SHEAVES

26:44.729 --> 26:47.691
SO THAT IT WILL DRY OUT,
THEN THRESH IT.

26:47.691 --> 26:50.485
AND HOW DO YOU EXPECT
TO THRESH THAT WHEAT?

26:50.485 --> 26:52.570
THE SAME WAY RUTH DID.

26:52.570 --> 26:54.531
"AND SHE GLEANED
UNTIL EVEN,

26:54.531 --> 26:57.909
"AND THEN SHE BEAT OUT
THAT SHE HAD GLEANED

26:57.909 --> 27:00.287
WITH FLAILS
AND WINNOWING."

27:03.039 --> 27:04.249
[SIGHS]

27:04.249 --> 27:05.959
WE HAVE TO DECIDE NOW.

27:05.959 --> 27:08.962
SHALL WE PUT IT TO A VOTE
WITH A SHOW OF HANDS?

27:10.672 --> 27:12.924
ALL THOSE IN FAVOR.

27:20.473 --> 27:22.934
ALL IN FAVOR WINS.

27:49.294 --> 27:51.588
MY BACK
IS KILLING ME,

27:51.588 --> 27:53.631
AND WE'RE GETTING
NOTHING DONE.

27:53.631 --> 27:55.717
WELL,
I'M LOSING FAT.

27:55.717 --> 27:57.052
[LAUGHING]

27:57.052 --> 27:59.179
WHAT DO YOU THINK
YOU'RE DOING, HOPE?

27:59.179 --> 28:02.599
I'M MAKING SHEAVES AND TYING THEM
SO THE GRAIN WILL DRY PROPERLY.

28:02.599 --> 28:05.685
I'LL GET TO YOURS IN
A MINUTE...IF YOU HAVE ANY.

28:05.685 --> 28:09.773
THEM SKIMPY THINGS,
YOU CALL THEM SHEAVES?

28:11.358 --> 28:13.026
THIS IS A WASTE.

28:13.026 --> 28:16.571
WE'RE NOT GOING TO GET
ENOUGH TO MAKE ANY FLOUR.

28:16.571 --> 28:19.407
COME WINTER, WE'RE ALL
GOING TO GO HUNGRY.

28:19.407 --> 28:21.659
WE CERTAINLY WILL
GO HUNGRY, WILLA,

28:21.659 --> 28:24.079
IF WE ALL WORK
LIKE YOU DO.

28:24.079 --> 28:26.915
YOU'RE GOING TO
HAVE TO TRY HARDER.

28:39.677 --> 28:41.179
HI, JACOB.

28:41.179 --> 28:42.389
CHARLIE.

28:42.389 --> 28:44.432
I NEED
SOME CAPS, TOM.

28:44.432 --> 28:46.017
ALL RIGHT.

28:46.017 --> 28:49.104
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
WITH ALL THE DYNAMITE?

28:49.104 --> 28:50.897
I'M A POWDER MONKEY.

28:50.897 --> 28:53.441
IT'S JUST LIKE DOUBLE
JACKING, YOU KNOW.

28:53.441 --> 28:55.485
NOT TOO MANY MEN WANT
THAT KIND OF WORK,

28:55.485 --> 28:58.655
AND ANYTIME I WANT A JOB,
I MOST TIMES CAN GET IT.

28:58.655 --> 29:00.782
WELL, I CAN SEE WHY.

29:00.782 --> 29:02.575
WELL, THE WIFE
MADE ME QUIT.

29:02.575 --> 29:05.453
SHE SAID SHE'D BE ABLE TO SLEEP
BETTER NIGHTS, YOU KNOW.

29:05.453 --> 29:08.206
SO I TOOK UP WHEAT FARMING.
WHEAT FARMING!

29:08.206 --> 29:10.291
YOU DON'T GET
BLOWN UP THAT WAY.

29:10.291 --> 29:12.377
YOU JUST GET
HAILED OUT.

29:12.377 --> 29:14.045
HERE YOU ARE.

29:14.045 --> 29:15.880
THANKS, TOM.

29:17.215 --> 29:20.051
WHAT DOES
POWDER MONKEY DO?

29:21.177 --> 29:23.096
OH, I'LL SHOW YOU.

29:23.096 --> 29:25.014
RIGHT...STICK OF
DYNAMITE, RIGHT?

29:25.014 --> 29:28.226
YOU CAN DROP IT, YOU CAN
BURN IT, YOU CAN STEP ON IT.

29:28.226 --> 29:29.394
NOTHING.

29:29.394 --> 29:32.230
TO MAKE IT EXPLODE,

29:32.230 --> 29:35.233
YOU NEED ONE OF
THESE...AND A FUSE.

29:35.233 --> 29:37.235
AND YOU STICK IT
ON THE END,

29:37.235 --> 29:40.363
AND YOU GOT TO CRIMP THE
CAP SO IT WON'T FALL OFF.

29:40.363 --> 29:43.575
YOU KNOW, WE GOT A TOOL FOR DOING
THAT, BUT HE WON'T USE IT.

29:43.575 --> 29:45.535
YOU'RE AN OLD WOMAN,
TOM.

29:45.535 --> 29:47.120
ANYWAY,
YOU TAKE THIS,

29:47.120 --> 29:50.248
AND YOU POKE IT
INTO THE DYNAMITE.

29:50.248 --> 29:52.417
WE CAN'T GET
ANY DRILLING DONE

29:52.417 --> 29:54.461
TILL YOU GET YOUR TOOLS
IN YOUR HAND,

29:54.461 --> 29:56.588
AND THE WORK IS THAT WAY.

29:56.588 --> 29:58.381
YES, TOM. YES, TOM.

29:58.381 --> 30:00.383
WE'RE GOING, TOM.

30:03.887 --> 30:07.932
Man: FIRE IN THE HOLE!
FIRE IN THE HOLE!

30:10.268 --> 30:12.729
[CLANK CLAN K]

30:49.432 --> 30:51.142
AHH.

31:15.708 --> 31:16.876
HOLD IT.

31:16.876 --> 31:19.379
LET'S TAKE A BREAK.

31:19.379 --> 31:22.799
JA, THAT'S GOOD.

31:24.008 --> 31:24.968
[SIGHS]

31:24.968 --> 31:26.386
A LITTLE WATER, HUH?

31:26.386 --> 31:27.554
AH, GOOD.

31:28.888 --> 31:30.557
HOW IS YOUR HAND?

31:30.557 --> 31:33.434
AH, JUST A LITTLE STIFF,
THAT'S ALL. FORGET IT.

31:33.434 --> 31:35.687
[SIGHS]

31:35.687 --> 31:37.021
AHH.

31:37.021 --> 31:39.899
I WORRY I DO IT
WORSE NEXT TIME.

31:39.899 --> 31:42.652
YOU WANT TO WORRY, WORRY
ABOUT THE DRILLING CONTEST

31:42.652 --> 31:44.529
AND HOW WE'RE
GOING TO WIN IT.

31:44.529 --> 31:45.697
US?

31:45.697 --> 31:48.575
US.

31:48.575 --> 31:50.118
YOU THINK WE CAN?

31:50.118 --> 31:53.413
FOR $50 IN PRIZE MONEY
SPLIT BETWEEN US,

31:53.413 --> 31:55.206
WE GOT TO WIN IT.

31:55.206 --> 31:57.208
OH,
I DON'T KNOW.

31:57.208 --> 31:59.085
ALL THEM
OTHER FELLAS...

31:59.085 --> 32:01.504
PRETTY GOOD.

32:01.504 --> 32:05.133
WELL, WE'RE
PRETTY GOOD, TOO,

32:05.133 --> 32:06.884
AND GETTING BETTER
EVERY DAY.

32:06.884 --> 32:08.553
[LAUGHS]

32:08.553 --> 32:09.971
HERE WE GO.

32:12.390 --> 32:14.267
THERE.

32:30.241 --> 32:32.327
WHAT'S THE MATTER,
CHARLIE?

32:33.703 --> 32:36.914
NOTHING.
JUST THINKING.

32:36.914 --> 32:40.043
ABOUT HOME AND THE WIFE
AND THE KIDS?

32:44.172 --> 32:47.175
THEY'VE JUST ABOUT
FINISHED SUPPER NOW.

32:47.175 --> 32:50.094
GOT THE DISHES
DONE...

32:51.471 --> 32:54.641
3 LITTLE GIRLS WILL BE
GETTING READY FOR BED.

32:57.268 --> 32:59.520
I MISS MY ELNA, TOO.

33:03.608 --> 33:06.653
MY PEGGY'S A SCRAPPER.
I MISS THAT.

33:06.653 --> 33:09.614
SHE'D HAVE TO BE
TO BE MARRIED TO YOU.

33:09.614 --> 33:11.282
[LAUGHING]

33:11.282 --> 33:14.494
SHE'S ALWAYS GMNG ME
WHAT FOR, YOU KNOW?

33:14.494 --> 33:17.288
DON'T CHANGE ME SHIRT,
DON'T CHANGE ME SOCKS...

33:17.288 --> 33:19.832
WHENEVER I COME HOME
LATE FOR SUPPER.

33:19.832 --> 33:22.001
YOU KNOW
WHAT THEY'RE LIKE.

33:23.461 --> 33:25.296
I MISS HER.

33:26.464 --> 33:28.424
MISS MY LAD.

33:28.424 --> 33:29.717
[SPITS]

33:35.306 --> 33:37.850
YOU GOT ANY
CHILDREN, JAKE?

33:37.850 --> 33:40.103
I DON'T KNOW.

33:40.103 --> 33:42.438
YOU DON'T KNOW?

33:44.899 --> 33:47.068
MY ELNA...

33:47.068 --> 33:49.153
[LAUGHING]

33:49.153 --> 33:51.197
MAYBE I HAVE BABY NOW.

33:51.197 --> 33:53.700
BEFORE I GET HOME,
FOR SURE.

33:53.700 --> 33:56.828
OH...THAT'S NICE.

33:57.912 --> 33:59.122
JA.

34:02.250 --> 34:05.086
THAT'S A SHAME YOU
CAN'T BE WITH HER.

34:05.086 --> 34:07.880
OH, I AM WITH HER...

34:07.880 --> 34:10.383
IN MY HEART.

34:10.383 --> 34:13.052
ALL OF THE TIME.

34:45.752 --> 34:47.962
Laura, voice-over:
TUESDAY WAS MAIL DAY.

34:47.962 --> 34:50.506
WE HAD TO WORK,
JUST LIKE ANY OTHER DAY.

34:50.506 --> 34:53.926
BUT ON TUESDAY, WORK HAD TO WAIT
UNTIL THE MAIL CAME...

34:53.926 --> 34:56.387
IF THERE WAS ANY.

34:57.847 --> 35:00.224
I'M MRS. ELNA JACOBSEN.

35:00.224 --> 35:02.810
HAVE I GOT A LETTER,
PLEASE?

35:04.395 --> 35:06.105
OH...

35:07.482 --> 35:08.775
OH!

35:24.916 --> 35:26.918
"DEAR FAMILY,

35:26.918 --> 35:29.128
"I WAS JUST SAYING
TO ONE OF MY NEW FRIENDS

35:29.128 --> 35:33.007
"THAT 100 MILES
IS NOT A LONG DISTANCE...

35:33.007 --> 35:37.720
EXCEPT WHEN IT LIES BETWEEN YOU
AND THE ONES YOU LOVE."

35:40.264 --> 35:43.768
"I VISIT WITH YOU EACH DAY
IN MY THOUGHTS,

35:43.768 --> 35:47.396
"AND I COUNT THE HOURS
UNTIL WE CAN...

35:47.396 --> 35:49.941
"BE TOGETHER AGAIN.

35:49.941 --> 35:52.777
"TAKE GOOD CARE
OF EACH OTHER.

35:52.777 --> 35:55.446
"KNOW THAT I AM WELL...

35:55.446 --> 35:57.907
"AND LOVE YOU ALL
VERY MUCH.

35:57.907 --> 35:59.492
CHARLES."

36:07.333 --> 36:09.794
WELL...PA'S ALL RIGHT.

36:09.794 --> 36:13.297
NOW WE HAVE TO GET
BACK TO WORK.

36:14.423 --> 36:16.050
COME ON.

36:16.050 --> 36:18.678
[SIGHS]

36:24.392 --> 36:26.227
OH, LOOK AT THAT.

36:26.227 --> 36:30.147
HE SPELLED THE VERY FIRST WORD WRONG.
D-E-R-E, DEAR.

36:30.147 --> 36:32.900
HA HA! AND ONE "G"
IN PEGGY!

36:32.900 --> 36:34.735
SPELLING.
SPELLING'S FOR GIRLS.

36:34.735 --> 36:36.779
YOU'RE GOING TO
LEARN HOW TO SPELL.

36:36.779 --> 36:38.406
I'D RATHER BE LIKE PA.

36:38.406 --> 36:40.199
WHY? BECAUSE
HE CAN'T SPELL?

36:40.199 --> 36:41.617
NO. BECAUSE HE'S THE BEST.

36:41.617 --> 36:44.328
THE BEST POWDER MONKEY
THIS SIDE OF THE MISSISSIPPI.

36:44.328 --> 36:45.371
YAH!

36:49.834 --> 36:51.460
[JACK LAUGHING]

36:51.460 --> 36:54.171
HEY! IT'S MONDAY!

36:54.171 --> 36:57.174
IT'S 8:00 IN THE MORNING!

36:57.174 --> 36:59.093
DAY AFTER TOMORROW'S
WEDNESDAY,

36:59.093 --> 37:00.887
AND WE'VE
DONE NOTHING YET.

37:00.887 --> 37:03.431
COME ON!
LET'S GET TO WORK!

37:03.431 --> 37:05.016
HA HA HA!

37:05.016 --> 37:06.767
[LAUGHING]

37:06.767 --> 37:09.520
ONE OF THESE DAYS, HE'S GOING TO
BLOW THIS WHOLE QUARRY OFF THE MAP.

37:09.520 --> 37:12.231
WE'LL BE OUT OF WORK
IF HE DO.

37:12.231 --> 37:14.817
HEY...HOW ABOUT THE 3 OF
US HAVING A FOOTRACE?

37:14.817 --> 37:16.777
THAT'S HOW YOU TELL
A GOOD MAN--

37:16.777 --> 37:18.905
WHEN HE'S GOT BOUNCE
AT THE END OF THE DAY.

37:18.905 --> 37:21.157
NOW, CHARLIE, JACOB... YOU'RE
ALL KEEPING BAD COMPANY.

37:21.157 --> 37:22.491
STOP IT!

37:22.491 --> 37:24.035
HEY!

39:06.554 --> 39:09.181
APRIL FOOL!
BACK TO WORK!

39:37.501 --> 39:39.170
DRILLERS,
GRAB YOUR STEEL.

39:39.170 --> 39:43.632
FIRST TEAM TO DRIVE THE WHITE
LINE TO THE ROCK WINS THE MONEY.

39:43.632 --> 39:45.176
GO AHEAD.

39:49.472 --> 39:51.223
Jack: COME ON, JACOB!

39:51.223 --> 39:53.225
COME ON, CHARLIE!

39:53.225 --> 39:56.187
EVERYBODY READY?

39:56.187 --> 39:57.271
Go!

39:57.271 --> 39:59.982
Jack: COME ON, CHARLIE!

39:59.982 --> 40:02.068
[MEN TALKING AND YELLING]

40:05.362 --> 40:07.490
Man: MOVE! HURRY UP!

40:07.490 --> 40:10.284
Jack: DRIVE IT,
CHARLIE! DRIVE IT!

40:17.708 --> 40:19.418
SWITCH!

40:20.503 --> 40:23.005
Jack: GET IN THERE,
JACOB! HIT!

40:25.466 --> 40:26.509
Jack: HIT!

40:26.509 --> 40:29.386
Man: COME ON!
DRIVE IT IN THERE!

40:37.561 --> 40:40.064
Jack: COME ON, JAKE!

41:06.006 --> 41:07.925
COME ON, JAKE...

41:07.925 --> 41:10.886
DRIVE IT!

41:12.972 --> 41:14.765
GO ON, JACOB!

41:18.394 --> 41:19.979
Jack: DRIVE IT IN!

41:19.979 --> 41:21.981
Go!

41:25.776 --> 41:28.779
Jack: COME ON, JAKE! GO!

41:28.779 --> 41:30.614
GO ON!
WE GOT 'EM!

41:31.699 --> 41:33.826
Go!

41:35.202 --> 41:36.287
Go!

41:36.287 --> 41:45.129
GO! GO!

41:45.129 --> 41:47.423
HOLD IT! HOLD IT!

41:47.423 --> 41:49.049
YOU WIN!

41:49.049 --> 41:50.718
WE GOT IT!

41:50.718 --> 41:52.011
[LAUGHING]

41:52.011 --> 41:55.055
ALL RIGHT, NOW, YOU'RE
GOING TO GET YOUR $50,

41:55.055 --> 41:57.433
BUT YOU'LL GET IT
WHEN YOU GET YOUR PAY,

41:57.433 --> 41:58.475
AND THAT'S NOT
FOR TWO DAYS YET.

41:58.475 --> 41:59.977
WE STILL GOT
WORK TO DO.

41:59.977 --> 42:03.564
COME ON, BOYS,
WORK'S A-WAITING!

42:03.564 --> 42:05.399
COME ON, LET'S GO!

42:05.399 --> 42:06.650
HEY!

42:12.740 --> 42:14.158
HEY...

42:14.158 --> 42:15.826
BIG WINNERS, RIGHT?

42:15.826 --> 42:17.119
Charles:
THAT'S RIGHT!

42:17.119 --> 42:18.579
HARD-ROCK MINERS,
RIGHT?

42:18.579 --> 42:19.747
RIGHT!

42:19.747 --> 42:22.541
YOU WERE LUCKY,
THAT'S ALL! HA HA!

42:22.541 --> 42:25.878
A REAL HARD-ROCK MINER
WOULDN'T LET YOU CARRY HIS--

42:29.423 --> 42:30.591
JACK!

42:30.591 --> 42:32.176
[ECHOING]

42:46.523 --> 42:49.735
Tom: HERE'S YOUR PAY...
AND THANKS FOR A GOOD JOB.

42:49.735 --> 42:51.070
YEAH.

42:51.070 --> 42:54.156
AND HERE'S YOUR $25
FOR WINNING THE DRILL-OFF.

42:54.156 --> 42:56.992
AND...JACK PETERS' PAY.

42:56.992 --> 43:01.538
SAY A WORD TO HIS WIFE FOR ME WHEN
YOU GIVE IT TO HER, WILL YOU?

43:03.540 --> 43:05.376
I'LL DO THAT.

44:05.102 --> 44:08.022
THIS IS WHERE
I TURN OFF.

44:15.112 --> 44:16.530
GOOD LUCK.

44:16.530 --> 44:17.990
THANK YOU.

44:17.990 --> 44:19.575
[DOG BARKING]

44:24.121 --> 44:27.124
GO ON. WHAT ARE
YOU WAITING FOR?

44:49.313 --> 44:51.440
Jacob: IT'S A BOY!

45:30.437 --> 45:33.232
[HORSE WHINNIES]

45:37.194 --> 45:38.529
PA...

45:40.531 --> 45:42.366
WHY, PA?

45:42.366 --> 45:44.076
[CRYING]

45:46.203 --> 45:48.080
PA...

45:48.080 --> 45:50.374
I THOUGHT YOU
WERE THE BEST.

45:52.709 --> 45:54.878
WHY, PA? WHY?

45:54.878 --> 45:56.880
I THOUGHT YOU
WERE THE--

46:06.640 --> 46:09.768
[SOBBING]

46:15.983 --> 46:19.570
I ONLY LIVE ABOUT
10 MILES FROM HERE. I...

46:19.570 --> 46:21.405
WELL, I MIGHT
STOP BY AND...

46:21.405 --> 46:25.075
SEE HOW YOU'RE GETTING ALONG
EVERY ONCE IN A WHILE, HUH?

46:33.000 --> 46:35.502
WELL, MAYBE YOU AND
YOUR MOM COULD COME OUT

46:35.502 --> 46:38.338
AND VISIT ME AND
MY FAMILY SOMETIME.

46:38.338 --> 46:42.092
GOT A LOT OF GOOD FISHING
AROUND OUR PLACE.

46:43.093 --> 46:46.430
YEAH, ALL RIGHT,
MR. INGALLS.

46:46.430 --> 46:48.599
WE'LL COME OVER.

46:48.599 --> 46:51.894
DON'T KNOW JUST WHEN.

46:51.894 --> 46:53.729
[SPITS]

46:57.483 --> 46:58.859
[SIGHS]

46:58.859 --> 47:00.652
NOW THAT MY PA DIED,

47:00.652 --> 47:02.946
GOT A LOT OF WORK
TO DO.

47:04.615 --> 47:06.658
LOT OF WORK TO DO.

47:48.492 --> 47:50.744
[JACK BARKING]

47:50.744 --> 47:53.539
Laura: MA! MA!

47:53.539 --> 47:57.793
PA'S BACK!
